pattern_2.text: I think that this study could be about a lot of things. I if was recorded in conjunction with the computer analysis, really anything could be measured to reasonable serve as a predictor of anything else. However, since I was rating relative "huskiness" of football players, it probably has to do something with width. Because there were different skin colors there may be a test to see if there is a bias towards one skin color for a particular rating or not. I did not see really any patterns in the experiment other than that which I manufactured for myself. For example, for a while I saw a skinny guy always followed by a fat guy, but then I saw brown and white alternating skin colors... I think that there may have been some sort of color and size perception pattern going on, though I am not sure as I placed my fingers on the screen (while still looking at the cross) to see if that would give me a constant to which I could relatively compare.
